{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"802bcbd8-19e2-4a0e-b473-99fd8ce188fe","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use **lifecycle event mappings** in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when app is partially obscured\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when app is no longer visible\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // Runs when app enters background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add the `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents` namespace.\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- `OnPause` fires when the activity loses focus; `OnStop` fires when it's fully hidden.\n- On iOS, `DidEnterBackground` is the direct equivalent.\n- Other useful hooks: `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnDestroy`, etc.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"21bfbf7c-db3f-41c8-98b2-c19f1e8ef1ec","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI, not a codebase-specific task. I can answer this directly.","outputTokens":394,"requestId":"7FCA:11463F:607D188:694CB96:69F156E2"},"id":"c94aa20c-0f28-41e3-b3a9-a8e68e3da077","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:55:06.376Z","parentId":"55f2957a-c3b8-4550-99bc-5f206707d3ca"}
